---
title: Automated Rollback Decision and Execution Workflow
---
flowchart LR
    signals["Observability signals<br/>Prometheus, K8s events, synthetic, business metrics"]
    catA["Category A immediate <60s<br/>5xx >5%, health fail, CrashLoop, OOM, DB pool"]
    catB["Category B escalated <15m<br/>p99 >2x, burn >10x, payment drop >2%, saturation"]
    catC["Category C manual decision<br/>customer reports, compliance anomaly, gradual degradation"]
    engine["Rollback decision engine<br/>correlate deployment + alert"]
    freeze["Freeze release<br/>stop canary expansion / block deploys"]
    traffic["Rollback execution<br/>route traffic to stable blue/green or previous image"]
    verify["Post-rollback verification<br/>smoke, metrics, synthetic, customer impact"]
    notify["Notify + incident record<br/>SRE, Release Manager, Compliance, postmortem"]
    evidence["Rollback evidence pack<br/>trigger, decision, timestamps, approvals"]
    signals --> catA
    signals --> catB
    signals --> catC
    catA -->|auto| engine
    catB -->|escalate/auto after window| engine
    catC -->|human approval| engine
    engine --> freeze
    freeze --> traffic
    traffic --> verify
    verify --> notify
    notify --> evidence
    verify -->|if still failing| engine
